cardano/transaction/OutputReference.title: OutputReference
cardano/transaction/OutputReference.description:
An `OutputReference` is a unique reference to an output on-chain. The `output_index`
 corresponds to the position in the output list of the transaction (identified by its id)
 that produced that output

core/datum/NftsConfiguration.title: NftsConfiguration
core/datum/NftsConfiguration.description:
Immutable NFT settings for oracle usage.
 Rationale for immutability:
 * utxo_ref - Ensures a unique policy ID for each oracle's NFT, preventing conflicts.
 * oracle_conf - Associates the NFT with a fixed oracle configuration, ensuring consistency.
 * oracle_script_hash - Links the NFT to a specific oracle script, maintaining a secure relationship.

fields.title: utxo_ref
fields.description: A reference to the UTXO, guaranteeing a unique policy ID for the oracle's NFTs.

fields.title: oracle_conf
fields.description: Defines parameters that the oracle will adhere to when using this validator.

fields.title: oracle_script_hash
fields.description: The hash of the oracle script ensuring a verifiable relationship between

core/datum/OracleConfiguration.title: OracleConfiguration
core/datum/OracleConfiguration.description:
Immutable oracle settings.
 Rationale for immutability:
 * platform_auth_nft - oracle deployment corresponds to one unchanging "platform"
 * pause_period_length - oracle nodes will be sure that platform won't update this to a make very short interval
 * reward_dismissing_period_length - oracle nodes will be sure that platform won't update this to a make very short interval
 * fee_token - oracle nodes will be sure that platform won't update reward currency

fields.title: platform_auth_nft
fields.description: platform is authorized by providing its input with specific NFT inside the transaction

fields.title: pause_period_length
fields.description: pause period is when oracle can no longer do aggregations, but rewards can still be calculated

fields.title: reward_dismissing_period_length
fields.description: after this period rewards can be dismissed with DismissRewards redeemer

fields.title: fee_token
fields.description: oracle fees are paid using this asset, if it's None then ada is used

core/datum/OracleDatum.title: OracleDatum
core/datum/OracleDatum.description:
There are four types of oracle utxos:
 0. AggState - each AggState utxo is complementary to RewardTransport, it contains the oracle feed value,
    that will be referenced by a user of a DApp.
 1. OracleSettings - one for each oracle,
    acts as single point of truth for oracle settings and node list.
 2. RewardAccount - one for each oracle,
    acts as single point of truth for reward distribution.
 3. RewardTransport - many for each oracle, with possibility of scaling their number on demand,
    users perform ODV aggregation with those by providing node feeds list constructed off-chain.

fields.title: nodes
fields.description: list of oracle nodes, node id is its FeedVkh

fields.title: required_node_signatures_count
fields.description: distinct node signatures number that passes multisig check

fields.title: aggregation_liveness_period
fields.description: aggregation is considered live, i.e. usable by dapps during this period

fields.title: time_uncertainty_aggregation
fields.description: max tx validity interval length for odv-aggregation tx

fields.title: time_uncertainty_platform
fields.description: max tx validity interval length for platform governance txs

fields.title: iqr_fence_multiplier
fields.description:
see interquartile range (IQR) and Tukey fences methods for outlier detection,
 recommended value for this parameter is 150 (i.e. 1.5) or 170 in case of normal distribution

fields.title: median_divergency_factor
utxo_size_safety_buffer
fields.description:
this value is always larger than zero,
 should be equal to a minimum ada amount held at maximum expected oracle utxo size

fields.title: pause_period_started_at
fields.description: if oracle is in pause state, then this field will have a certain timestamp value

core/datum/PriceData.title: PriceData
core/datum/PriceData.description:
The main data structure representing price-related information.
 It can contain shared, extended, or generic data.

fields.title: nodes_to_rewards
fields.description:
Maps oracle node feed verification keys to their reward amounts.
 Each entry represents an individual node's accumulated rewards that can be claimed.
 WARNING nodes_to_rewards mapping should be sorted ascendingly by FeedVkh, to use it with aikens dict.from_ascending_pairs

fields.title: last_update_time
fields.description: The last time when rewards were distributed or UTxO was spent/updated

core/redeemer/MintingRedeemer.title: MintingRedeemer
core/redeemer/MintingRedeemer.description:
Types of actions for Oracle NFTs (protocol tokens)
 * MintToken  - Oracle start: one time mint for CoreSettings and RewardAccount; any number of mints for RewardTransport and AggState
 * ScaleToken - Scale RewardTransport and AggState UTxOs: any number of mints/burns for RewardTransport and AggState
 * BurnToken  - Oracle remove: all tokens are burned

core/redeemer/RewardRedeemer.title: RewardRedeemer
core/redeemer/RewardRedeemer.description:
Distinguishes between different redeemer types who can collect oracle fees.
 See RedeemRewards constructor, which also points to corresponding output index.

core/redeemer/SettingsRedeemer.title: SettingsRedeemer
core/redeemer/SettingsRedeemer.description:
Types of actions for Oracle smart contract
 * OdvAggregate - user sends on demand validation request together with oracle nodes message collected off-chain
 * NodeCollect - oracle node collects rewards
 * PlatformCollect - oracle platform collects rewards
 * ManageSettings - oracle platform updates configuration or lifecycle:
   - UpdateSettings changes consensus, timing or fee settings
   - AddNodes adds new operators
   - DelNodes removes operators
   - PauseOracle starts pause period so nodes can finalise pending rewards
   - ResumeOracle cancels pause, resuming normal operation
   - RemoveOracle destroys the remaining oracle state after pause window elapses
 * ScaleDown - oracle platform burns RewardTransport and AggState NFTs, destroying corresponding UTxOs
 * DismissRewards - oracle platform turns RewardTransport UTxOs with pending rewards calculations into NoRewards
